This paper deals with the complexity of the $k$-Coloring problem parameterized by clique-width and modular treewidth, which are both graph parameters. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves algorithms and running times, which suggests it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, which could lead to a classification under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
